n for administrators to remove successfully.","pos":[107550,107689]},{"content":"If the signed code integrity policy is manually enabled and copied to the CodeIntegrity folder, to remove the policy, you must complete the following steps:","pos":[107690,107846]},{"pos":[107849,107966],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>  For reference, signed code integrity policies should be replaced and removed from the following locations:"},{"content":"EFI System Partition<ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;gt;\\\\</ph>Microsoft<ph id=\"ph2\">\\\\</ph>Boot","pos":[107976,108017]},{"content":"OS Volume<ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;gt;\\\\</ph>Windows<ph id=\"ph2\">\\\\</ph>System32<ph id=\"ph3\">\\\\</ph>CodeIntegrity","pos":[108028,108075]},{"pos":[108083,108219],"content":"Replace the existing policy with another signed policy that has the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>6 Enabled: Unsigned System Integrity Policy<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> rule option enabled."},{"pos":[108226,108405],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>  To take effect, this policy must be signed with a certificate previously added to the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>UpdatePolicySigners<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> section of the original signed policy you want to replace."},{"content":"Restart the client computer.","pos":[108411,108439]},{"content":"Verify that the new signed policy exists on the client.","pos":[108445,108500]},{"pos":[108507,108664],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>  If the signed policy that contains rule option 6 has not been processed on the client, the addition of an unsigned policy may cause boot failures."},{"content":"Delete the new policy.","pos":[108670,108692]},{"content":"Restart the client computer.","pos":[108698,108726]},{"content":"If the signed code integrity policy has been deployed using by using Group Policy, you must complete the following steps:","pos":[108728,108849]},{"pos":[108855,109002],"content":"Replace the existing policy in the GPO